        <abstract>
        <ref type="biblio" target="Radich2012">241ff</ref> dates this scripture to ca.
                286. The "Lifespan" chapter contains the earliest statements ... that the lifespan
                of the current Buddha of this world-system is in fact measureless or infinite. ...
                it seems clear that Śākyamuni himself is in fact immortal, and his apparent
                parinirvāṇa is a docetistic show.</abstract>
